Que 5)What Are Templates in Angular?
-------------------------------------
A template in Angular is the HTML part of a component.
It tells Angular:
👉 What to show on the screen, 👉 How to display the data
You can think of a template as the view (UI) of a component.
🏦 Simple Example
Suppose we have a Banking component.
Component (Logic - TypeScript)
export class AccountComponent {
  balance = 50000;
}
Template (HTML - View)
<h2>My Account</h2>
<p>Balance: {{ balance }}</p>
👉 {{ balance }} is an Angular expression.
👉 Angular takes the value from the component and shows it in the browser.
So:
Component → Contains logic
Template → Displays data
✅ Two Ways to Create Template in Angular
1️⃣ Inline Template
The HTML is written directly inside the component file.
Example:
@Component({
  selector: 'app-account',
  template: `
    <h2>My Account</h2>
    <p>Balance: {{ balance }}</p>
  `
})
export class AccountComponent {
  balance = 50000;
}
📌 Here, HTML is written inside the template property using backticks ( ).
✔ Used for small templates
❌ Not good for large UI
2️⃣ Linked Template (External Template)
The HTML is written in a separate .html file.
Example:
account.component.ts
@Component({
  selector: 'app-account',
  templateUrl: './account.component.html'
})
export class AccountComponent {
  balance = 50000;
}
account.component.html
<h2>My Account</h2>
<p>Balance: {{ balance }}</p>
✔ Cleaner and more professional
✔ Better for large applications
✔ Mostly used in real projects
🔥 Simple Difference
Inline Template	Linked Template
HTML inside component file	HTML in separate file
Used for small UI	Used for large UI
Uses template property	Uses templateUrl property

Que 6) : What is AOT (Ahead-of-Time) Compiler in Angular?
----------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Compiles Code Before Running the App
AOT compiler converts Angular TypeScript and HTML templates into pure JavaScript during build time, before the app is loaded in the browser.
2️⃣ Runs During Build Process
When you run:
ng build --prod
Angular uses AOT to compile the application.
3️⃣ Faster Application Loading
Since the code is already compiled before reaching the browser, the browser does less work.
👉 This makes the application load faster.
4️⃣ Reduces Runtime Errors
AOT checks templates and code during build time.
If there is any mistake, it shows an error before deployment.
Example:
If you write wrong property name in template:
{{ balnce }}
It will give error during build.
5️⃣ Smaller Bundle Size
AOT removes unnecessary Angular compiler code from the final build.
👉 This reduces file size.
6️⃣ Better Security
Templates are compiled earlier, so there is less risk of injection attacks.

Ques 7) What is Just-In-Time (JIT) Compilation?
------------------------------------------------
1️)Compilation at Runtime
JIT compiles the Angular application in the browser when the app loads.
2️)Happens During Execution
The Angular compiler runs just before the application starts, converting templates and TypeScript into JavaScript.
3️)Used in Development Mode
When we run ng serve, Angular uses JIT compilation by default.
4️)Faster Development Builds
It does not require a full build process, so changes reflect quickly during development.
5️)Slower Initial Loading
Since compilation happens in the browser, the app takes more time to load compared to AOT.
6️)Errors Appear at Runtime
Template or code errors are detected while the application is running in the browser.
👉 JIT is mainly used for development because it provides quick builds but is not recommended for production.

