Que 11) What is @Output() in Angular?
--------------------------------------
1️⃣ @Output() is used to send data from child component to parent component.
2️⃣ It uses an EventEmitter to send events.
3️⃣ Data flow direction:
👉 Child → Parent
🏦 Example
Child Component (transfer.component.ts)
@Output() transferDone = new EventEmitter<string>();
sendData() {
  this.transferDone.emit("Transfer Successful");
}
Parent Component (dashboard.component.html)
<app-transfer (transferDone)="showMessage($event)"></app-transfer>
Parent TypeScript
showMessage(message: string) {
  console.log(message);
}
Now when child emits event, parent receives it.
🔥 Simple Difference
@Input()	@Output()
Parent → Child	Child → Parent
Receives data	Sends data
Used for property binding	Used for event binding
🎯 Easy Memory Trick
👉 Input = Data comes IN
👉 Output = Data goes OUT

