Que 17) Explain One-Way Data Binding in Angular ?
--------------------------------------------------
One-way data binding in Angular means data flows in a single direction only — either from the component to the view or from the view to the component. It does not automatically synchronize both sides.
Angular supports one-way binding in three ways:
✅ 1️⃣ Interpolation – {{ data }}
(Component ➝ View)👉 Used to display data from component in HTML.
Component   name = "Mahesh";
HTML <p>{{ name }}</p>
What Happens? Angular takes name from component and shows it in HTML.
✔ Output: Mahesh
✔ Data flows: Component ➝ View
✅ 2️⃣ Property Binding – [property]="data"
(Component ➝ View)
👉 Used to set HTML property value from component.
Component isDisabled = true;
HTML <button [disabled]="isDisabled">Click Me</button>
What Happens?
If isDisabled = true → button is disabled.
If isDisabled = false → button is enabled.
✔ Data flows: Component ➝ View
✅ 3️⃣ Event Binding – (event)="method()"
(View ➝ Component)
👉 Used to send event from HTML to component.
HTML <button (click)="showMessage()">Click</button>
Component
showMessage() {
  alert("Button Clicked");
}
What Happens?
When button is clicked → method runs in component.
✔ Data flows: View ➝ Component

