Que 19) What are Angular Lifecycle Hooks?
------------------------------------------
Angular lifecycle hooks are special methods that allow us to run code at different stages of a component’s life, such as 
initialization (ngOnInit), data change (ngOnChanges), and destruction (ngOnDestroy).
a component also has stages:
Create → Update → Destroy
Angular gives us hooks (methods) to run code at these stages.
🔹 Important Lifecycle Hooks (Simple)
1️⃣ ngOnInit()
✔ Runs once
✔ Called when component is created
✔ Used to load data (API call, initialization)
ngOnInit() {
  console.log("Component Initialized");
} 👉 Runs when component loads.
2️⃣ ngOnChanges()
✔ Runs when input property changes
✔ Used when parent sends data to child component
ngOnChanges() {
  console.log("Input value changed");
} 👉 Runs whenever input data changes.
3️⃣ ngOnDestroy()
✔ Runs before component is removed
✔ Used to clean memory (unsubscribe, clear timer)
ngOnDestroy() {
  console.log("Component Destroyed");
}
👉 Runs when component is removed from screen.

