Inject ChangeDetectorRef:
constructor(private cd: ChangeDetectorRef) {}
Then call:
this.cd.markForCheck();
This tells Angular:
👉 “Please check this component again.”
🧠 How to Debug (Simple Steps)
Check if OnPush is used
Check if object is mutated directly
Ensure new object reference is created
Use markForCheck() if needed
🎯 Simple Summary
With Default strategy → Angular checks everything
With OnPush strategy → Angular checks only when reference changes
✅ In one line:
If a component using OnPush is not updating, make sure to change the object reference or manually trigger change detection using ChangeDetectorRef.

